entry.title: Mitigate sharing of permissions with webview StoragePartition
entry.content:
Currently, granted permissions are scoped to a profile, so any

permissions granted in a regular tab are granted profile-wide, including

to non-default StoragePartitions.



To mitigate unpartitioned sharing of permissions in the webview case, we

preemptively drop any permission queries from a webview for permissions

that the webview could not have legitimately been granted.



Bug: 1462709

entry.title: shimless_rma: Use non-OTR profile for 3p diag
entry.content:
CreateProfileAsync() returns OTR profile if the profile has not yet been

created. This cause the extension not be activated.

Convert it to the original profile before installing extensions and

IWAs.

When installing extension to a OTR profile, it will be installed to the

original profile and won't be activate in OTR profile by default.

Because ShimlessRMAAppProfile is only for a ShimlessRMA session, we can

set it to ephemeral to fully remove it and don't need to use OTR

profile.

Also add a polling check to make sure the extension's service worker is

ready before launching the IWAs. This make sure the extension is really

activate.

inside the class, to allow its creation outside of SceneController.

entry.title: Revert "[ios/sign-in sheet] Re-write account cookie waiting"
entry.content:
This reverts commit f6678948ddbf1202fbeb008c108c27a856f443dd.



Example failure: https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/ios-simulator-full-configs/48471/overview

Reason for revert: Suspected cause of newly introduced flakiness of

`ConsistencyPromoSigninCoordinatorTestCase`.



Original change's description:

> [ios/sign-in sheet] Re-write account cookie waiting

>

> No behavior change for most practical cases. The CL might also be a

> bug fix for some speculative scenarios, more details below.

>

> Context: When accounts.google.com is opened, a bottom sheet is shown

> to offer browser sign in. If the user taps its primary button, the

> sheet waits until the account cookie is populated, then closes itself.

> It might also show an error dialog instead, in case of an auth error or

> timeout.

>

> Before this CL, this was implemented as follows:

> 1. ConsistencyPromoSigninMediator observed the IdentityManager for

> its entire lifetime.

> 2. Upon getting an OnAccountsInCookieUpdated() notification, it

> checked whether a) there was no auth error, b) there was a primary

> account, and c) the cookie jar was non-empty. If all 3 were

> satisfied, it closed the sheet.

>

> This approach has some problems, at least theoretically.

> - In 1, more than one notification might arrive. Or a notification

entry.title: Fix tablet mode controller requesting machine state too early
entry.content:
Tablet mode controller sends DBus request to powerd daemon for getting

the lid and detachable base status, then update the UI accordingly.

However, powerd may not be ready for the first time tablet controller

asking the status, thus the machine always stays in clamshell mode.



Update the tablet mode controller via overriding the

`PowerManagerBecameAvailable` member function, and perform requesting

switch status in it. With overriding this function, the first time

switch request is ensured to be sent after the powerd daemon is ready.



BUG=b:283533859
